[
  {
    "start": 0.0,
    "end": 1.24,
    "text": "I'm Adrian from AWS."
  },
  {
    "start": 1.8,
    "end": 3.34,
    "text": "And I'm Absar from Infinitium."
  },
  {
    "start": 3.52,
    "end": 4.48,
    "text": "This is my architecture."
  },
  {
    "start": 14.040000000000001,
    "end": 15.8,
    "text": "Absar, thanks for joining us today."
  },
  {
    "start": 15.96,
    "end": 17.98,
    "text": "So you're in the online payments industry."
  },
  {
    "start": 18.48,
    "end": 19.22,
    "text": "What does that entail?"
  },
  {
    "start": 19.48,
    "end": 20.02,
    "text": "Thank you, Adrian."
  },
  {
    "start": 20.240000000000002,
    "end": 25.2,
    "text": "At Infinitium, we serve more than 180 million card users"
  },
  {
    "start": 25.2,
    "end": 28.22,
    "text": "specifically for online e-commerce transactions."
  },
  {
    "start": 28.22,
    "end": 31.88,
    "text": "And one of the biggest challenges that we face is fraud."
  },
  {
    "start": 32.28,
    "end": 33.04,
    "text": "Let's dive in."
  },
  {
    "start": 33.32,
    "end": 33.64,
    "text": "Absolutely."
  },
  {
    "start": 34.24,
    "end": 36.56,
    "text": "So we have this authentication system"
  },
  {
    "start": 36.56,
    "end": 39.5,
    "text": "that we are integrating our fraud detection system with."
  },
  {
    "start": 39.62,
    "end": 41.66,
    "text": "So during the payment authentication flow,"
  },
  {
    "start": 42.14,
    "end": 43.4,
    "text": "the fraud detection kicks in."
  },
  {
    "start": 43.5,
    "end": 46.04,
    "text": "We have Amazon CloudFront"
  },
  {
    "start": 46.04,
    "end": 48.099999999999994,
    "text": "because our customers are throughout the region."
  },
  {
    "start": 48.94,
    "end": 51.980000000000004,
    "text": "AWS WAFs helps us be secure"
  },
  {
    "start": 51.980000000000004,
    "end": 54.04,
    "text": "against many common vulnerabilities."
  },
  {
    "start": 56.04,
    "end": 57.099999999999994,
    "text": "From the CloudFront,"
  },
  {
    "start": 57.1,
    "end": 59.620000000000005,
    "text": "the requests are routed to our load balancer"
  },
  {
    "start": 59.620000000000005,
    "end": 61.54,
    "text": "that helps us upkeeping"
  },
  {
    "start": 61.54,
    "end": 65.7,
    "text": "with the scalability aspects of it,"
  },
  {
    "start": 66.1,
    "end": 70.76,
    "text": "which goes all the way to our ECS cluster."
  },
  {
    "start": 71.02,
    "end": 71.22,
    "text": "Right."
  },
  {
    "start": 71.28,
    "end": 74.18,
    "text": "This is where the brains of the system is."
  },
  {
    "start": 74.4,
    "end": 76.5,
    "text": "Now, I understand you had version 1.0."
  },
  {
    "start": 76.68,
    "end": 77.68,
    "text": "What were some of the challenges"
  },
  {
    "start": 77.68,
    "end": 78.62,
    "text": "you were trying to overcome?"
  },
  {
    "start": 78.62,
    "end": 83.14,
    "text": "Yes. 1.0 had been an on-premises solution"
  },
  {
    "start": 83.14,
    "end": 85.38000000000001,
    "text": "that was difficult to scale."
  },
  {
    "start": 85.98,
    "end": 88.7,
    "text": "And one key consideration was that"
  },
  {
    "start": 88.7,
    "end": 93.34,
    "text": "1.0 had standard transitional parameters,"
  },
  {
    "start": 93.78,
    "end": 96.46000000000001,
    "text": "while for our enhanced rule processing,"
  },
  {
    "start": 96.98,
    "end": 101.56,
    "text": "we needed to have enhanced metrics around those rules."
  },
  {
    "start": 101.56,
    "end": 105.98,
    "text": "So we are talking about more than 290 rules"
  },
  {
    "start": 105.98,
    "end": 108.78,
    "text": "that we now support with FDA 2.0."
  },
  {
    "start": 108.92,
    "end": 109.14,
    "text": "Okay."
  },
  {
    "start": 109.24000000000001,
    "end": 110.86,
    "text": "So how do you actually deploy those containers"
  },
  {
    "start": 110.86,
    "end": 111.56,
    "text": "into the environment?"
  },
  {
    "start": 112.18,
    "end": 112.42,
    "text": "Right."
  },
  {
    "start": 112.54,
    "end": 113.88,
    "text": "So we have a development process"
  },
  {
    "start": 113.88,
    "end": 117.82000000000001,
    "text": "where all our microservices are in separate repositories,"
  },
  {
    "start": 118.22,
    "end": 121.68,
    "text": "and they go through a CI-CD process,"
  },
  {
    "start": 122.08,
    "end": 125.7,
    "text": "which then gets those containers deployed into ECR,"
  },
  {
    "start": 125.7,
    "end": 130.32,
    "text": "and that's where our ECS cluster pulls them from."
  },
  {
    "start": 130.6,
    "end": 130.8,
    "text": "Right."
  },
  {
    "start": 130.86,
    "end": 132.7,
    "text": "So you have all your images sitting up there."
  },
  {
    "start": 132.84,
    "end": 133.94,
    "text": "So you could have chosen"
  },
  {
    "start": 133.94,
    "end": 135.38,
    "text": "lots of different compute classes."
  },
  {
    "start": 135.68,
    "end": 137.44,
    "text": "Why did you choose AWS Fargate?"
  },
  {
    "start": 137.74,
    "end": 138.74,
    "text": "We are a small, humble team,"
  },
  {
    "start": 139.12,
    "end": 142.46,
    "text": "and the last thing that we wanted to do"
  },
  {
    "start": 142.46,
    "end": 145.72,
    "text": "was manually maintain the systems and deployments."
  },
  {
    "start": 146.22,
    "end": 149.98000000000002,
    "text": "So we decided to just focus on the development process"
  },
  {
    "start": 149.98000000000002,
    "end": 151.98000000000002,
    "text": "and getting the product out in the market"
  },
  {
    "start": 151.98,
    "end": 155.64,
    "text": "while Fargate helped us host those services"
  },
  {
    "start": 155.64,
    "end": 159.64,
    "text": "without the need to essentially actively patch"
  },
  {
    "start": 159.64,
    "end": 161.38,
    "text": "or maintain the deployments."
  },
  {
    "start": 161.62,
    "end": 163.56,
    "text": "Also using Graviton instances, right?"
  },
  {
    "start": 164.1,
    "end": 164.7,
    "text": "Yes, we are,"
  },
  {
    "start": 164.73999999999998,
    "end": 165.79999999999998,
    "text": "because that's what provides us"
  },
  {
    "start": 165.79999999999998,
    "end": 167.64,
    "text": "a better price-performance ratio."
  },
  {
    "start": 167.78,
    "end": 171.14,
    "text": "So I see you using also lots of different data services here,"
  },
  {
    "start": 171.23999999999998,
    "end": 173.66,
    "text": "and I see Amazon Neptune, a graph database."
  },
  {
    "start": 174.1,
    "end": 175.0,
    "text": "What are you using that for?"
  },
  {
    "start": 175.5,
    "end": 175.67999999999998,
    "text": "Yes."
  },
  {
    "start": 175.82,
    "end": 180.73999999999998,
    "text": "So Neptune helps us manage more complexities of the transaction."
  },
  {
    "start": 180.74,
    "end": 183.8,
    "text": "Because in your traditional transaction,"
  },
  {
    "start": 184.0,
    "end": 185.70000000000002,
    "text": "you have multiple components."
  },
  {
    "start": 186.22,
    "end": 187.36,
    "text": "So you have transaction information,"
  },
  {
    "start": 187.5,
    "end": 188.4,
    "text": "your user information,"
  },
  {
    "start": 188.9,
    "end": 189.78,
    "text": "your device information,"
  },
  {
    "start": 189.9,
    "end": 190.5,
    "text": "these are interconnected."
  },
  {
    "start": 191.12,
    "end": 192.62,
    "text": "This makes one set of transaction."
  },
  {
    "start": 193.16,
    "end": 194.24,
    "text": "Now, with graph,"
  },
  {
    "start": 194.54000000000002,
    "end": 197.08,
    "text": "we don't only look at this particular transition,"
  },
  {
    "start": 197.08,
    "end": 201.82000000000002,
    "text": "but also the historic anecdotes of this transition."
  },
  {
    "start": 201.98000000000002,
    "end": 204.92000000000002,
    "text": "For example, the velocity of this card"
  },
  {
    "start": 204.92000000000002,
    "end": 207.62,
    "text": "or things of historic nature."
  },
  {
    "start": 207.62,
    "end": 209.20000000000002,
    "text": "And with graph database,"
  },
  {
    "start": 209.34,
    "end": 212.16,
    "text": "we are able to traverse end depth"
  },
  {
    "start": 212.16,
    "end": 214.12,
    "text": "with comparatively better latency"
  },
  {
    "start": 214.12,
    "end": 216.38,
    "text": "as compared with other databases."
  },
  {
    "start": 216.6,
    "end": 217.86,
    "text": "So graph is a lot more efficient"
  },
  {
    "start": 217.86,
    "end": 219.56,
    "text": "when it comes to this sort of complexity"
  },
  {
    "start": 219.56,
    "end": 221.52,
    "text": "and dependency structure that you have, right?"
  },
  {
    "start": 221.62,
    "end": 221.98000000000002,
    "text": "It is."
  },
  {
    "start": 222.18,
    "end": 224.8,
    "text": "So while graph helps us get into"
  },
  {
    "start": 224.8,
    "end": 226.52,
    "text": "extended transactional insights,"
  },
  {
    "start": 226.84,
    "end": 229.5,
    "text": "it's also important to use the technology"
  },
  {
    "start": 229.5,
    "end": 230.5,
    "text": "that's fit for the purpose."
  },
  {
    "start": 230.5,
    "end": 233.42,
    "text": "So while Neptune helps us look at those insights,"
  },
  {
    "start": 233.72,
    "end": 235.32,
    "text": "we also use DocumentDB"
  },
  {
    "start": 235.32,
    "end": 236.92,
    "text": "to store our policies,"
  },
  {
    "start": 237.34,
    "end": 238.56,
    "text": "our rules."
  },
  {
    "start": 239.04,
    "end": 239.9,
    "text": "And at times,"
  },
  {
    "start": 239.96,
    "end": 241.92,
    "text": "we also flatten this information"
  },
  {
    "start": 241.92,
    "end": 244.0,
    "text": "into DocumentDB for different purposes."
  },
  {
    "start": 244.22,
    "end": 244.92,
    "text": "Amazon RDS."
  },
  {
    "start": 245.22,
    "end": 245.96,
    "text": "How are you using that?"
  },
  {
    "start": 246.14,
    "end": 248.2,
    "text": "So while we have all of this"
  },
  {
    "start": 248.2,
    "end": 250.8,
    "text": "contemporary functionalities"
  },
  {
    "start": 250.8,
    "end": 252.56,
    "text": "that are looking into transition insights"
  },
  {
    "start": 252.56,
    "end": 253.96,
    "text": "or managing the policies and rules,"
  },
  {
    "start": 254.22,
    "end": 255.86,
    "text": "we also have the traditional functionality"
  },
  {
    "start": 255.86,
    "end": 258.7,
    "text": "of providing some of the interfacing"
  },
  {
    "start": 258.7,
    "end": 259.44,
    "text": "through a CMS"
  },
  {
    "start": 259.44,
    "end": 260.7,
    "text": "to manage this information."
  },
  {
    "start": 261.14,
    "end": 262.92,
    "text": "So organization data and user data."
  },
  {
    "start": 263.3,
    "end": 264.52000000000004,
    "text": "And that traditional information"
  },
  {
    "start": 264.52000000000004,
    "end": 267.2,
    "text": "is then capped over the RDS."
  },
  {
    "start": 267.46000000000004,
    "end": 267.90000000000003,
    "text": "So obviously,"
  },
  {
    "start": 267.90000000000003,
    "end": 269.16,
    "text": "this whole system needs"
  },
  {
    "start": 269.16,
    "end": 270.92,
    "text": "a lot of low latency processing,"
  },
  {
    "start": 271.12,
    "end": 272.22,
    "text": "Amazon MemoryDB."
  },
  {
    "start": 272.98,
    "end": 273.74,
    "text": "How are you using that?"
  },
  {
    "start": 274.14,
    "end": 274.44,
    "text": "Exactly."
  },
  {
    "start": 274.64,
    "end": 275.8,
    "text": "So while all the systems"
  },
  {
    "start": 275.8,
    "end": 277.52000000000004,
    "text": "are very good at what they do,"
  },
  {
    "start": 278.22,
    "end": 279.5,
    "text": "MemoryDB with Redis"
  },
  {
    "start": 279.5,
    "end": 280.78000000000003,
    "text": "is also providing us"
  },
  {
    "start": 280.78000000000003,
    "end": 281.90000000000003,
    "text": "microsecond latency"
  },
  {
    "start": 281.90000000000003,
    "end": 284.14,
    "text": "in different aspects."
  },
  {
    "start": 284.14,
    "end": 284.76,
    "text": "For example,"
  },
  {
    "start": 284.82,
    "end": 285.56,
    "text": "one of them being"
  },
  {
    "start": 285.56,
    "end": 287.56,
    "text": "we have our microservices here"
  },
  {
    "start": 287.56,
    "end": 289.28,
    "text": "that are being authenticated"
  },
  {
    "start": 289.28,
    "end": 291.3,
    "text": "by an authentication service."
  },
  {
    "start": 291.84,
    "end": 294.36,
    "text": "Once those are authenticated,"
  },
  {
    "start": 294.76,
    "end": 296.28,
    "text": "we save the authentication information"
  },
  {
    "start": 296.28,
    "end": 296.9,
    "text": "in Redis."
  },
  {
    "start": 297.24,
    "end": 298.46,
    "text": "And that helps us process"
  },
  {
    "start": 298.46,
    "end": 300.08,
    "text": "the subsequent requests very fast."
  },
  {
    "start": 300.46,
    "end": 300.82,
    "text": "So Absal,"
  },
  {
    "start": 300.86,
    "end": 302.21999999999997,
    "text": "you're in a regulated environment."
  },
  {
    "start": 302.65999999999997,
    "end": 303.94,
    "text": "How has this actually helped you deliver?"
  },
  {
    "start": 304.26,
    "end": 305.14,
    "text": "With FDS,"
  },
  {
    "start": 305.4,
    "end": 306.76,
    "text": "we also had to be PCI,"
  },
  {
    "start": 306.82,
    "end": 307.53999999999996,
    "text": "DSS compliant."
  },
  {
    "start": 307.8,
    "end": 309.02,
    "text": "And a lot of services"
  },
  {
    "start": 309.02,
    "end": 311.86,
    "text": "we noticed were compliance ready."
  },
  {
    "start": 312.41999999999996,
    "end": 313.86,
    "text": "And that kind of helped us"
  },
  {
    "start": 313.86,
    "end": 315.66,
    "text": "go to market much faster."
  },
  {
    "start": 316.3,
    "end": 316.44,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 316.56,
    "end": 317.86,
    "text": "So AWS is taking care"
  },
  {
    "start": 317.86,
    "end": 318.64,
    "text": "of all that for you."
  },
  {
    "start": 319.12,
    "end": 319.56,
    "text": "Fantastic."
  },
  {
    "start": 320.1,
    "end": 320.34000000000003,
    "text": "Absal,"
  },
  {
    "start": 320.40000000000003,
    "end": 321.36,
    "text": "thank you for sharing"
  },
  {
    "start": 321.36,
    "end": 322.46000000000004,
    "text": "your architecture with us."
  }
]